<setup>
  <selectFromSequence name="m" from="-1" to="1" step="0.5" exclude="0"/>
  <number name="b">-2*$m</number>
  <selectFromSequence name="c" from="3" to="4" step="1"/>
  
  <piecewiseFunction symbolic="false" name="f"> 
    <function domain="(-1,$c)"><math simplify>$m*x + $b</math></function>
    <function domain="[$c, 7)"><math simplify>-$m*(x-$c) + ($m*$c+$b)</math></function>
  </piecewiseFunction>
 
  <piecewiseFunction symbolic="false" name="A"> 
    <function domain="(-1,$c)"><math simplify>$m/2*x^2 + $b*x - (2*$m+2*$b)</math></function>
    <function domain="[$c, 7)"><math simplify>-$m/2*(x-$c)^2 + ($m*$c+$b)*x - ($m*$c+$b)*$c + $m/2*$c^2 + $b*$c - (2*$m+2*$b)</math> </function>
  </piecewiseFunction>  

  <piecewiseFunction symbolic="false" name="B"> 
    <function domain="(-1,$c)"><math simplify>$m/2*x^2 + $b*x</math></function>
    <function domain="[$c, 7)"><math simplify>-$m/2*(x-$c)^2 + ($m*$c+$b)*x - ($m*$c+$b)*$c + $m/2*$c^2 + $b*$c</math> </function>
  </piecewiseFunction>  
  
  <number name="z1">2</number>
  <number name="z2">2*$c + $b/$m</number>
  <mathList name="Ints1">(-1,$z1) ($z2,7)</mathList>
  <math name="Int2">($z1,$z2)</math>
  <math name="Int3">(-1,$c)</math>
  <math name="Int4">($c,7)</math>
</setup>

<graph xmin="-1" xmax="7" ymin="-4" ymax="4" grid="1 1" fixAxes="true" showNavigation="false">
  $f
  <label anchor="($c,$m*$c+$b + 0.3*($m*$c+$b))"><m>f</m></label>
</graph>  


<p>
  Let <m>A(x) = \int_2^x f(t) \, dt</m>, where <m>f</m> is the piecewise linear function whose graph is given.
</p>   

<p>
  <ol marker="a.">
    <li>
      <p>
        On what intervals within <m>-1 \lt x \lt 7</m> is <m>A</m> increasing? decreasing?  If there is more than one interval, separate them with commas; if there are none, enter <em>none</em>.  Use interval notation: for example, enter <q><m>(2,6)</m></q> for <q><m>2 \lt x \lt 6</m></q>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <m>A</m> is increasing on <mathInput name="incrAEntered"/> 
        <answer unorderedCompare>
          <award><when> 
            ($incrAEntered = $Ints1 and $m < 0) or ($incrAEntered = $Int2 and $m > 0) 
          </when></award>
        </answer>
      </p>  
      <p>
        <m>A</m> is decreasing on <mathInput name="decrAEntered"/> 
        <answer unorderedCompare>
          <award><when> 
            ($decrAEntered = $Ints1 and $m > 0) or ($decrAEntered = $Int2 and $m < 0) 
          </when></award>
        </answer>
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        On what intervals within <m>-1 \lt x \lt 7</m> is <m>A</m> concave up? concave down?  If there is more than one interval, separate them with commas; if there are none, enter <em>none</em>.  Use interval notation: for example, enter <q><m>(2,6)</m></q> for <q><m>2 \lt x \lt 6</m></q>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <m>A</m> is concave up on <mathInput name="CCUAEntered"/> 
        <answer unorderedCompare>
          <award><when> 
            ($CCUAEntered = $Int3 and $m > 0) or ($CCUAEntered = $Int4 and $m < 0) 
          </when></award>
        </answer>
      </p>  
      <p>
        <m>A</m> is concave down on <mathInput name="CCDAEntered"/> 
        <answer unorderedCompare>
          <award><when> 
            ($CCDAEntered = $Int4 and $m > 0) or ($CCDAEntered = $Int3 and $m < 0) 
          </when></award>
        </answer>
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Complete the following table of values for <m>A(x)  = \int_2^x f(t) \, dt</m>.
      </p>
        <table suppressTableNameInTitle="true"> 
    <tabular left="minor" right="minor" top="minor" bottom="minor" valign="middle" halign="center">
     <row>
      <cell><m>x</m></cell>
      <cell>0</cell>
      <cell>1</cell>
      <cell>2</cell>
      <cell>3</cell>
      <cell>4</cell>  
      <cell>5</cell>  
      <cell>6</cell>  
     </row>
     <row>
      <cell><m>A(x)</m></cell>
      <cell><answer>$$A(0)</answer></cell>
      <cell><answer>$$A(1)</answer></cell>
      <cell><answer>$$A(2)</answer></cell>
      <cell><answer>$$A(3)</answer></cell>  
      <cell><answer>$$A(4)</answer></cell>  
      <cell><answer>$$A(5)</answer></cell> 
      <cell><answer>$$A(6)</answer></cell> 
     </row>
    </tabular>
  </table> 
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Now suppose that <m>B(x)  = \int_0^x f(t) \, dt</m>.  Complete the following table of values for <m>B(x)</m>.
      </p>
        <table suppressTableNameInTitle="true"> 
    <tabular left="minor" right="minor" top="minor" bottom="minor" valign="middle" halign="center">
     <row>
      <cell><m>x</m></cell>
      <cell>0</cell>
      <cell>1</cell>
      <cell>2</cell>
      <cell>3</cell>
      <cell>4</cell>  
      <cell>5</cell>  
      <cell>6</cell>  
     </row>
     <row>
      <cell><m>B(x)</m></cell>
      <cell><answer>$$B(0)</answer></cell>
      <cell><answer>$$B(1)</answer></cell>
      <cell><answer>$$B(2)</answer></cell>
      <cell><answer>$$B(3)</answer></cell>  
      <cell><answer>$$B(4)</answer></cell>  
      <cell><answer>$$B(5)</answer></cell> 
      <cell><answer>$$B(6)</answer></cell> 
     </row>
    </tabular>
  </table> 
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Observe that  
        <me>B(x)  = \int_0^x f(t) \, dt = \int_0^2 f(t) \, dt + \int_2^x f(t) \, dt = \int_0^2 f(t) \, dt + A(x).</me>
        The value of <m>\int_0^2 f(t) \, dt = </m> <mathInput name="const" /> <answer><award><when>$const = 2*$m + 2*$b</when></award></answer>, and this shows that the difference between <m>A(x)</m> and <m>B(x)</m> is <answer><choiceInput inline>
          <choice>?</choice>
          <choice credit="1">a constant</choice>
          <choice>zero</choice>
          <choice>their shape</choice>
        </choiceInput></answer>. 
          
      </p>
    </li>
  </ol>  

</p>  